Implementation techniques

- Parallel radix partitioning shape (per-thread histograms + serial
  prefix scan + parallel scatter) mirrors DuckDB's and polars's
  published design, adapted to Arrow-backed buffers.
- Block-quicksort's branchless partition concept (Edelkamp & Weiss)
  informed the branchless scatter in compute/sort_radix.go; no
  code copied.
- American Flag Sort (McIlroy, Bostic, McIlroy) informed the in-place
  MSD radix sketches in the design docs; the shipping path is LSD.
